node.text:
IT'S THE NPS-AVERSARY!
From the early days of "hey, maybe we should keep this place wild", through pivotal moments of the very fabric of modern American history, the NPS continues to protect and preserve the places that make us who we are. 
Today marks 103 years of National Parks Service – we think a toast is in order! Video by @maxeyfish #radparks #findyourpark

node.title: The (unofficial) History of the National Parks

node.accessibility_caption: Canyon views from the summit of Angel's Landing in Zion National Park.

node.text:
Talk about a bird's-eye view 🦅
One of the most popular hikes in @zionnps, Angel's Landing is a strenuous 5.4-mile (8 km) round trip hike that leads to some of the most spectacular views in the canyon. With long drop-offs, steep inclines, and narrow trails, this hike is not for the faint of heart.

Heading out to Zion? Summertime means peak visitation, so be sure to pack your patience and have a backup plan. Need some help? Check out our park finder for additional activities and nearby parks. #findyourpark #radparks #leaveitbetter

node.text: We need nature as much as nature needs us to be good stewards. We’re all about leaving our lands healthier and more vibrant than we found them—that’s why we teamed up with our buddies at @leavenotracecenter to create a collection in celebration of taking care of nature. #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

node.text: Our favorite weekend escape has to be stargazing in Joshua Tree 🌠 Inspired by the International Dark Star park, our Escape to Nature Pocket Tee features national parks around the country. #findyourpark #radparks #leaveitbetter

node.text:
Pastel skies and wildflower blooms, who could ask for more 😍 @sequoiakingsnps is comprised of roughly 95% protected and managed wilderness with over 800 miles of trails to explore. Remember to practice safe hiking when backpacking, and always follow Leave No Trace principles! #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark
